article.headline: Belmont 85, Kennesaw St. 66
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Henry Harris shot a career-high 23 points to lift Belmont over Kennesaw State 85-66 on Saturday. The Bruins (14-8, 8-3 Atlantic Sun Conference) went on an early roll scoring 17 of the first 19 points in the game. Kennesaw State (8-15, 4-7) scored 27 points off Belmont's 22 turnovers, but couldn't turn that into a lead. Golden Ingle scored 14 points for the Owls, which shot just 35 percent from the field and missed 13 out of 16 from beyond the arc. Kennesaw State bounced back from halftime down 27-37 and shortened Belmont's lead by scoring eight points off turnovers in two minutes. Justin Hare added 20 points and Shane Dansby shot 12 points for Belmont. Andre Morgan shot 12 points for Kennesaw State.
